  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which suburbs are considered Brisbane's inner east?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Brisbane's inner east generally covers Bulimba, Hawthorne, Balmoral, Morningside, Cannon Hill, Camp Hill, Coorparoo, East Brisbane, Norman Park, and Seven Hills. The strip follows the river bend east from the CBD and shares strong school catchments, character housing, and a pedestrian-friendly retail culture that distinguishes it from Brisbane's northern and southern suburbs."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do properties in Brisbane's inner east sell off-market?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. A meaningful share of quality inner east properties sell before or shortly after they appear on the major portals. Buyers who have registered their brief with an active inner east agent are contacted first when a matching property becomes available. Portal-only buyers regularly miss these opportunities."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What flood and zoning issues should inner east buyers check?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Buyers should check Brisbane City Council's flood overlay maps for river flooding near Hawthorne, Bulimba, and Kangaroo Point, and separately check Bulimba Creek catchment overlays for properties in Morningside, Cannon Hill, and Camp Hill. Heritage character overlays affect what can be done to older Queenslanders. Properties near Coorparoo, Stones Corner, and Cannon Hill activity centres may sit inside or adjacent to higher-density zoning."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What school catchments add value in Brisbane's inner east?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Balmoral State School is one of the most sought-after state primary catchments in Brisbane and has a direct effect on prices for homes in Balmoral and parts of Hawthorne. Anglican Church Grammar School (Churchie) in East Brisbane draws buyers from across the inner east and beyond. Buyers focused on specific catchments should verify addresses directly with the school rather than relying on suburb boundaries, which do not always align with catchment lines."
      }
    }
  ]
